Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:37.871 --> 00:39.646
<i>Don't tell me they canceled your trip.</i>

00:39.806 --> 00:41.581
The first direct flight
from New York to London?

00:41.741 --> 00:43.550
Pan Am wouldn't cancel this
for the Second Coming.

00:43.710 --> 00:46.589
- So you're checking <i>up on</i> me?
- Damn right. How's my magazine?

00:46.746 --> 00:49.522
Well, Back of the Book's
given me shit-all.

00:49.682 --> 00:53.357
Front copy's more white than black,
and I'm waiting for a photo dump...

00:53.520 --> 00:55.158
<i>...from Stockton. Typical Saturday.</i>

00:55.321 --> 00:57.460
- Where's Art stand on the cover?
- Almost there.

00:58.091 --> 00:59.570
I, um...

00:59.926 --> 01:01.906
I have some lingering concerns.

01:02.529 --> 01:07.103
- About the cover art or about my story?
- Your story is a smear piece.

01:07.267 --> 01:10.043
Five hundred Vietnamese civilians
were murdered, unprovoked.

01:10.203 --> 01:11.546
<i>That warrants smearing.</i>

01:11.704 --> 01:14.048
We do not have confirmation
from the military.

01:14.207 --> 01:17.051
My source has seen
the Army's preliminary report.

01:17.210 --> 01:19.486
Look, in a matter of weeks
this is public record.

01:19.646 --> 01:22.149
<i>Let's wait tiâ€œ then.
I want to know we're right...</i>

01:22.315 --> 01:24.659
<i>...before we start tarnishing
these men's careers.</i>

01:24.818 --> 01:28.061
<i>We got Cafley, Mitchell, Bernhardt.</i>

01:28.221 --> 01:30.098
<i>Jesus, Bernhardfs 23 years old.</i>

01:30.256 --> 01:33.100
- I don't care if he's in diapers.
- Finn.

01:34.961 --> 01:37.703
We've been scooped on Songmy
before because you preached caution.

01:38.098 --> 01:40.339
<i>If you need substantiation
to sleep at night...</i>

01:40.500 --> 01:44.141
...get General Peers on the phone,
then run my fucking story.

01:46.606 --> 01:47.607
Okay, Chief.

01:47.774 --> 01:49.481
<i>When the galley's locked,
wire it to London.</i>

01:49.642 --> 01:51.986
I'll head to the bureau
as soon as we touch down.

01:53.847 --> 01:55.349
Motherfucker. Angie.

01:57.050 --> 01:59.394
Get General William Peers,
U.S. Army, on the phone.

01:59.552 --> 02:02.897
Tell him I need a confirmation
of a story before we go to press tonight.

02:04.023 --> 02:06.264
Finn's centerpiece on Songmy?

02:06.526 --> 02:07.937
Yes.

02:08.094 --> 02:09.630
<i>Know what gets me? The arrogance.</i>

02:09.795 --> 02:12.504
We can disagree.
It's not as if I'm above discourse.

02:12.665 --> 02:16.704
He doesn't like it when I dust off
my press pass and write about Vietnam.

02:16.870 --> 02:18.144
He's a hawk.

02:18.304 --> 02:19.339
A military apologist.

02:25.111 --> 02:26.681
Here you go.

02:30.950 --> 02:34.830
I read that there's a lounge
in the upper deck with a full bar.

02:34.988 --> 02:38.299
Fire off this Editor's Page on the flight,
wire it home when we land.

02:38.458 --> 02:40.995
Hopefully sneak it
into this week's issue.

04:04.677 --> 04:07.055
Where do you wanna start?

04:07.213 --> 04:10.626
I don't know. Cindy, I am so excited.

04:10.783 --> 04:13.787
If we talk to two girls a day,
we can have the entire magazine...

04:13.953 --> 04:16.024
...in a couple of weeks.

04:16.189 --> 04:18.533
Oh, what about Vivian?

04:18.690 --> 04:19.761
Um...

04:19.926 --> 04:22.736
She calls me Cindy Lou Who.

04:22.929 --> 04:24.101
In a rude way.

04:24.264 --> 04:27.711
We're gonna have to talk to a lot of girls.
That means even the rude ones.

04:28.701 --> 04:31.409
Why don't you talk to Dottie in Theater?

04:32.305 --> 04:33.750
I don't really know Dottie.

04:34.407 --> 04:35.477
She's on your yes list.

04:35.942 --> 04:38.923
Because she is always complaining,
not because we're friends.

04:39.078 --> 04:41.115
I can't do all the recruitment on my own.

04:41.414 --> 04:42.654
Oh, I know.

04:42.815 --> 04:43.919
I know.

04:44.083 --> 04:45.892
Oh, I'll talk to Beverly.

04:46.052 --> 04:47.793
That'll give us half of Foreign.

04:49.088 --> 04:51.068
I think she's making it with her reporter.

04:51.291 --> 04:54.465
Well, maybe, but she gave me
her tuna crunch casserole once...

04:54.627 --> 04:55.765
...and it was delicious.

04:55.928 --> 04:57.032
Mm.

04:57.930 --> 04:59.876
What about Jane?

05:00.033 --> 05:02.035
You know, a lot of the girls
look up to her.

05:04.470 --> 05:06.040
I talked to Jane.

05:06.205 --> 05:07.411
I don't think she's ready.

05:07.707 --> 05:09.118
Oh...

05:09.275 --> 05:12.347
All right, well, I will focus on Beverly.

05:17.617 --> 05:18.618
Cindy, what is that?

05:21.254 --> 05:22.824
Oh, it's--

05:23.890 --> 05:27.531
They were handing them out
at the last consciousness-raising...

05:27.694 --> 05:32.905
...and it is about giving
and receiving pleasure.

05:33.066 --> 05:34.545
My little girl is all grown up.

05:36.002 --> 05:37.675
I can't read more
than a paragraph at a time...

05:37.837 --> 05:39.475
...because it makes me blush.

05:42.108 --> 05:43.849
It's happening now, isn't it?

05:45.044 --> 05:46.148
Damn it.

06:10.336 --> 06:12.543
- Those my profiles?
- Eldridge Cleaver...

06:12.705 --> 06:15.015
...David Hilliard, Angela Davis.

06:15.174 --> 06:16.744
Nice suit. Who died?

06:16.909 --> 06:19.753
Oh, James P. Kelly, 63rd precinct.

06:19.912 --> 06:23.553
PD got into a gunfight with a group
of Black Panthers in Midwood.

06:23.716 --> 06:27.095
- One of the officers died.
- Oh, boy.

06:37.397 --> 06:39.001
You have something. What is it?

06:39.165 --> 06:40.667
Do you know anyone in Vietnam?

06:41.267 --> 06:45.010
- I could find a list of active servicemen.
- No, personally. Do you know any vets?

06:45.738 --> 06:48.446
The boys I grew up with
went to college to avoid the war.

06:48.608 --> 06:50.645
- Did Finn sign off on a story?
- Sort of.

06:50.810 --> 06:53.620
On his way out last night,
he came over, tapped on my desk...

06:53.780 --> 06:55.555
...and said,
"When Our Boys Come Home."

06:55.715 --> 06:57.388
And then he walked out the door.

06:57.550 --> 06:58.756
"When our boys come home"?

06:58.918 --> 07:01.626
- How is that an investigative piece?
- I have no idea.

07:02.054 --> 07:04.261
When were you gonna tell me
you had a boyfriend?

07:04.424 --> 07:05.425
What?

07:05.892 --> 07:08.236
Townley Investments? Chad, is it?

07:09.328 --> 07:10.705
Who told you?

07:10.863 --> 07:11.864
Not you.

07:14.500 --> 07:16.070
Four Panthers were killed too.

07:16.235 --> 07:18.511
They don't mention that
till the last paragraph.

07:18.671 --> 07:20.981
It's articles like this
that give them a bad name.

07:21.140 --> 07:24.952
I think it's dead policemen
that give the Panthers a bad name.

07:25.111 --> 07:27.591
Are you writing
a pro-law enforcement article now?

07:28.080 --> 07:31.789
- Patti, I'm not gonna argue with you.
- I'm not arguing. I'm just asking.

07:31.951 --> 07:33.794
I'm not writing a pro-anything article.

07:33.953 --> 07:36.524
There's violence on both sides.
I'm not gonna ignore it.

07:39.358 --> 07:41.770
So, what time is the funeral?

07:41.928 --> 07:43.839
Tonight at 6, near Prospect.

07:43.996 --> 07:45.942
Rhodes, you're going
to a funeral tonight?

07:47.500 --> 07:48.672
Yeah.

07:48.835 --> 07:50.212
You need something to do?

07:50.670 --> 07:52.149
We publish on a Saturday.

07:52.305 --> 07:54.410
You planning on bringing a typewriter
to the funeral parlor?

07:54.574 --> 07:57.145
We're not publishing tonight.
Finn gave us leeway on the deadline.

07:57.310 --> 07:58.448
- Leeway?
- I'm sorry...

07:58.611 --> 08:00.113
...that sounds like
an investigative piece.

08:00.279 --> 08:02.122
Really?
Doug, does that sound...

08:02.281 --> 08:03.453
...like an investigative piece to you?

08:03.616 --> 08:07.029
You know, I hadn't thought of it, Patti,
but it kind of does.

08:07.353 --> 08:08.661
But that's Sam's assignment.

08:09.288 --> 08:10.733
Right.

08:10.890 --> 08:12.233
How's that coming along?

08:13.025 --> 08:14.663
An ongoing story is a privilege.

08:14.827 --> 08:18.639
It's not something that you back into
when you can't close on deadline.

08:18.798 --> 08:20.277
Reporters.

08:21.434 --> 08:22.504
In my office.

08:31.511 --> 08:33.957
We may need an alternative
from the feature well...

08:34.113 --> 08:36.150
...in the next few hours.

08:36.549 --> 08:38.085
I thought the Peers report
was our centerpiece.

08:38.518 --> 08:40.691
It was, but that story might not make it.

08:40.852 --> 08:45.666
So I wanna go around here
and see which story you might have...

08:45.825 --> 08:46.929
...that we can slot in.

08:47.093 --> 08:49.573
Why would Finn ix-nay his own story?

08:51.097 --> 08:53.168
Nobody is ix-naying anything.

08:53.332 --> 08:56.370
I'm preparing a contingency
in case this story unravels...

08:56.536 --> 08:57.742
...at the eleventh hour.

08:57.904 --> 09:01.545
Does Finn know
that you're preparing a contingency?

09:01.707 --> 09:03.186
He's on an airplane.

09:03.342 --> 09:06.186
I am in charge.
And I'm gonna make damn sure...

09:06.345 --> 09:10.452
...that this magazine lives up
to its sterling reputation.

09:11.584 --> 09:14.190
- Who's got something?
- You think somebody's fired?

09:14.353 --> 09:16.697
If Wick was letting a reporter go,
he wouldn't call them all in.

09:16.856 --> 09:19.063
- Unless they're all fired.
- Don't be ridiculous.

09:19.225 --> 09:20.761
That happened at The Register.

09:20.927 --> 09:23.066
They fired everyone but the typesetter
and the guy on Obits.

09:23.229 --> 09:25.402
But they hired them all back
the next day.

09:25.598 --> 09:28.078
Angie, what's going on up there?

09:28.234 --> 09:30.373
All hands on deck.
I'm sure your reporters will fill you in.

09:30.536 --> 09:31.708
Angie.

09:36.175 --> 09:38.553
Wick is working on a backup
for the Songmy story.

09:38.711 --> 09:40.622
He wants everything
Ned has from the week.

09:40.780 --> 09:42.691
Why? Finn's story was brilliant.

09:43.115 --> 09:45.026
Wick doesn't think it'll hold water.

09:46.752 --> 09:49.494
I know. But once Finn lands,
this will all get sorted out.

09:49.655 --> 09:51.828
Looks like for now it's double duty.

09:53.292 --> 09:54.930
Thank you, gentlemen.

10:00.132 --> 10:01.975
Captions?

10:02.134 --> 10:03.204
This is scandalous.

10:03.369 --> 10:04.905
Captions are Cindy Reston's job.

10:05.071 --> 10:06.744
Wick needs more than she can handle.

10:06.906 --> 10:10.046
You don't take the magazine's
star reporter and assign him captions.

10:10.209 --> 10:12.314
Which is why I need you to do it.

10:12.545 --> 10:14.786
Wick's letting Doug follow
his investigative track...

10:14.947 --> 10:16.949
...while Adam and Ralph
prep their features.

10:17.116 --> 10:20.120
That's generous.
Doug hasn't had a cover in months.

10:20.286 --> 10:23.358
Yeah, it means I really need
to get my vets piece up and running.

10:23.522 --> 10:25.798
Okay. Well, I'll call the VA...

10:25.958 --> 10:28.029
...and I'll have something set up
with their press office.

10:28.194 --> 10:30.936
Actually, I'm gonna work
with Naomi on this one.

10:31.697 --> 10:32.698
Ralph's Naomi?

10:32.865 --> 10:35.402
She's got a husband in Da Nang.
She might have insight.

10:35.568 --> 10:37.570
And you don't know
anyone in Vietnam, right?

10:37.737 --> 10:39.341
- But I could--
- Hey, captions.

10:55.955 --> 10:58.265
We set off on a...

11:00.493 --> 11:05.101
Terry, what's a $5 word
for trip or journey?

11:05.264 --> 11:07.710
- Uh, traverse?
- A noun, not a verb.

11:07.867 --> 11:10.473
Like, "We set out on a..." On a what?

11:11.103 --> 11:12.104
How about a sojourn?

11:12.972 --> 11:15.145
- Too sanctimonious.
- Odyssey.

11:17.376 --> 11:18.821
Venture.

11:19.245 --> 11:22.249
Pilgrimage, peregrination.

11:22.415 --> 11:24.895
Although peregrination
is a $10 word.

11:25.051 --> 11:26.621
What's going on with you?

11:28.487 --> 11:30.899
I don't know why I imagined
this would be different.

11:32.058 --> 11:33.833
What would be different?

11:35.494 --> 11:36.666
You said vacation.

11:36.996 --> 11:38.532
- That's what you said.
- Talia--

11:38.698 --> 11:41.702
They give the magazine these tickets
in exchange for a story.

11:41.867 --> 11:44.643
That's how quid pro quo works.

11:46.138 --> 11:49.745
And thank you.
"Pilgrimage" was the word.

11:56.148 --> 11:58.856
This is not what I told you to write.

11:59.018 --> 12:00.258
This is exactly
what you told me to write.

12:00.419 --> 12:02.695
If it's what I told you,
I didn't mean it. Go, go.

12:02.855 --> 12:04.232
Come on.

12:06.759 --> 12:08.432
- Vivian, hi.
- Yes?

12:08.594 --> 12:11.302
Your article
on the Milan Bank Bombing.

12:11.464 --> 12:13.876
- I really dug it.
- Swell. Thanks. But I just got--

12:14.033 --> 12:17.276
"It's as if Jupiter himself
cast his thunderous judgment...

12:17.436 --> 12:19.643
...upon the Piazza Fontana."

12:19.805 --> 12:22.081
Just guessing that JP didn't write that.

12:22.241 --> 12:23.584
The man's a bonobo.

12:24.477 --> 12:27.651
Sometimes he writes,
"Insert metaphor here" in his copy.

12:27.813 --> 12:30.817
- I'd like to insert a metaphor somewhere.
- Wow.

12:30.983 --> 12:33.987
Listen, some of the girls and I
are getting together after work.

12:34.153 --> 12:35.689
Just to blow off some steam.

12:35.855 --> 12:38.495
It's at that place on Madison,
the Women's Commerce Shop?

12:38.657 --> 12:41.501
- That little craft store?
- Yeah, they have good sandwiches.

12:41.660 --> 12:44.038
The guys never go,
so it's a good place to talk...

12:44.196 --> 12:47.871
...if you like sandwiches
and you want to get away from JP.

12:48.367 --> 12:49.539
Sure.

12:49.702 --> 12:50.840
Hey, Vivian.

12:51.370 --> 12:52.576
Um...

12:52.738 --> 12:54.411
Don't mention this to anyone, okay?

13:00.913 --> 13:02.392
You have to imagine I'm looking
at a bunch of people...

13:02.548 --> 13:04.585
...with sweaty chests.
All I see are sweaty chests.

13:04.750 --> 13:06.354
And in front of me is Willie Reed.

13:06.519 --> 13:09.398
So he's just talking.
He's jawing with his buddies...

13:09.555 --> 13:11.193
...and what I didn't realize...

13:11.357 --> 13:13.496
...is that his girlfriend
was right behind me.

13:13.659 --> 13:15.161
- Uh-huh.
- So his eyes light up.

13:15.728 --> 13:18.732
He puts out his arms,
and I just-- I go right in.

13:18.898 --> 13:20.605
You did not hug Willis Reed.

13:20.766 --> 13:24.043
I did.
I completely misread the situation.

13:24.203 --> 13:26.979
Okay, you need to tell me
what does Willis Reed smell like.

13:27.139 --> 13:28.641
Who's Willis Reed?

13:30.609 --> 13:32.486
Uh, a three-time All-Star.

13:33.345 --> 13:35.484
- The center for the Knicks.
- Oh.

13:35.648 --> 13:38.219
And how does he relate
to "When Our Boys Come Home"?

13:39.552 --> 13:41.691
Well, we sort of hit
a standstill on the story.

13:41.921 --> 13:42.991
A standstill.

13:43.789 --> 13:45.894
My husband won't be back
for eight months.

13:46.058 --> 13:48.299
Glad to see you're not
too broken up about it.

13:48.460 --> 13:50.497
Would you like me to call the VA now?

13:50.663 --> 13:53.507
No. I don't want anyone
hand-picked by the military.

13:53.666 --> 13:54.804
<i>Okay-</i>

13:54.967 --> 13:57.379
- Could you review my captions?
- Sure. I'll swing by in a minute.

13:57.536 --> 13:59.982
I'm meeting my mother
for lunch in 20 minutes.

14:00.139 --> 14:03.143
Well, then, clearly we need
to expedite these captions.

14:04.243 --> 14:06.587
Okay. Let me see where you stand.

14:08.547 --> 14:09.924
Thank you.

14:10.416 --> 14:11.417
Thanks for your help.

14:13.652 --> 14:14.892
He's frustrated.

14:15.054 --> 14:16.055
That's all.

14:16.222 --> 14:18.725
Finn rejected all of his proposals
for the investigative piece...

14:18.891 --> 14:20.802
...and then gave him
a nothing assignment.

14:21.227 --> 14:23.798
I mean, "When Our Boys Come Home"?

14:23.963 --> 14:26.409
That's an idea. It's not a story.

14:27.132 --> 14:29.772
We don't know any
Vietnam veterans, do we?

14:30.569 --> 14:32.480
I wish your father
had gotten you a job...

14:32.638 --> 14:35.118
...at a less Jewish magazine.

14:35.674 --> 14:37.449
I know you find the newsroom dynamic.

14:37.610 --> 14:40.887
Mommy, none of the editors
at News of the Week are Jewish...

14:41.046 --> 14:43.117
...and only a few of the reporters are.

14:43.282 --> 14:44.625
Yours is.

14:50.723 --> 14:52.225
Anyway...

14:52.892 --> 14:53.962
I stopped by the pharmacy...

14:54.126 --> 14:56.970
...and Dr. Simpson gave me
an extra prescription of Obetrol.

14:57.763 --> 15:00.369
He says it is better
than your Aminorex, stronger.

15:01.367 --> 15:03.677
You take a pill
a half hour before meals...

15:03.836 --> 15:06.373
...and it'll curb your appetite. Heh.

15:09.708 --> 15:11.915
You know, I'm really sorry.
I have to run.

15:12.444 --> 15:15.482
It's deadline day,
and I should get back to the office.

15:15.714 --> 15:17.887
Thank you for lunch, Mommy.

15:21.854 --> 15:23.424
Give Daddy my best.

